Since Eq. (\ref{Tot}) is even with respect to $\mu$, it is clear that
the fermion spin does not contribute in the induced vacuum charge in the subcritical regime.
Moreover, such a (spin) problem has a physical meaning  in the subcritical range only, when
the expression for induced vacuum charge can be expanded in ascending power series of $a, \alpha$.

